{"word":"H6679 - צוּד - tsûwd - tsood - Chase","slug":"H6679","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">צוּד</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>tsûwd"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>tsood"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Chase"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E6;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05D3; - tsu&#x0302;d</b> - <i>tsood</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>lie</i> alongside (that is, in wait); by implication to <i>catch</i> an animal (figuratively men); (denominative from <a href=\"#/H6718\">H6718</a>) to <i>victual</i> (for a journey): - chase, hunt, sore, take (provision)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6718\">H6718</a>, <a href=\"#/H6720\">H6720</a>, <a href=\"#/H6737\">H6737</a>"}]}